During winter 2014–15, GII.17 was reported as the predominant norovirus strain in China, accounting for 67.2% of outbreaks, whereas during the following winter (2015–16), the proportion of GII.17 outbreaks decreased to 25.0% (

  36
 ). We found that GII.2[P16] viruses caused an increase in the number of norovirus outbreaks during winter 2016–17. The first GII.2[P16]–positive sample was detected in August 2016 in Guangdong Province (

